&lt;h2 id="final-thoughts">Final Thoughts
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>There’s still a lot of work to do and the result isn’t exactly “professional,” but I’m happy with how it is now. HUGO is honestly a great tool for people like me. It&amp;rsquo;s super flexible if you want to build everything yourself, and super easy if you use a theme. The fact that everything is written in Markdown is amazing, I love the format. It’s all clean, readable files that are easy to edit and organize.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It might technically be better to keep the blog and the website in separate projects, but that would mean more overhead. Right now, I can easily relate projects to posts. We’ll see how this scales once I have a larger number of posts, though I’m not sure I’ll ever reach that point.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>All the content on my site, including theme modifications, is public on my GitHub repo. Hosting the site on GitHub is honestly super easy.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Hope you liked the new site and the behind-the-scenes! My goal was to unify the blog and the site visually, and I think I’ve done that. For now, the site will stay like this, and I’m really looking forward to jumping back into my other projects.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>See you next time!&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>